{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/embed-base64-encoded-images-inline-in-html","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"ddcfa166-075a-5b07-84c8-281ee277d666","html":"<p>Here is how you can embed an image in HTML inline. This is similar to how you embed an image in a HTML email message.</p>\n<p><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"html_inline_image.png\" title=\"html_inline_image.png\"></p>\n<p>To create one you will need to encode you image file as base64 and then embed that base64-encoded image as follows…</p>\n<p>&#x3C;img src=”data:&#x3C;MIMETYPE>;base64,&#x3C;BASE64_ENCODED_IMAGE>”></p>\n<p>&#x3C;img src=”data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANS… (see source for full base64 encoded image) …8bgAAAAASUVORK5CYII=”></p>\n<p>The up-side is that the image is stored with the HTML, so if you download a webpage’s HTML, it is packaged with the image files in one single file. That also means one single request to the server, and no separate request for the image file.</p>\n<p>The down-side is that the image is base64 encoded, so it is much larger than it’s binary sibling. This makes the use of this rather limited.</p>\n<h2 id=\"resources\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#resources\" aria-label=\"resources permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Resources</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc2397\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">RFC2397 – The “data” URL scheme</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Data_URI_scheme\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Wikipedia – Data URI scheme</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"comment\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#comment\" aria-label=\"comment permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Comment</h2>\n<div id=\"comments\">\n  <ol class=\"comment-list\">\n    <li id=\"comment-223983\" class=\"comment even thread-even depth-1 comment reader\">\n      <img alt=\"Base64 Image\" src=\"https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/0501df3c813883759ff60ee864721fe5?s=80&amp;d=https%3A%2F%2F0.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D80&amp;r=PG\" class=\"avatar avatar-80 photo\" height=\"80\" width=\"80\">\n      <div class=\"comment-meta comment-meta-data\">\n        <div class=\"comment-author vcard\">\n          <cite class=\"fn\" title=\"https://www.base64image.org\">Base64 Image</cite>\n        </div>\n        <!-- .comment-author .vcard -->\n        <abbr class=\"comment-date\" title=\"Thursday, February 27th, 2014, 12:14 pm\">February 27, 2014</abbr> at <abbr class=\"comment-time\" title=\"Thursday, February 27th, 2014, 12:14 pm\">12:14 pm</abbr>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"comment-text\">\n        <p>I recommend Base64 Image  web tool to encode image to base64.</p>\n      </div>\n      <!-- .comment-text -->\n    </li>\n    <!-- .comment -->\n  </ol>\n  <!-- .comment-list -->\n</div>\n<style class=\"grvsc-styles\">\n  .grvsc-container {\n    overflow: auto;\n    position: relative;\n    -webkit